works.description: For years unknown, dollhouses have always been a special part of childrens’ earliest years, but if it is something like Coleen Moore’s Fairy Castle, it sure would find a place in a museum like the Museum of Science + Industry, Chicago. Our earlier coverage of dollhouses includes the Elaine Shaw dollhouse that was equipped with all modern functional equipment, and the Bespoken dollhouse that featured the select work of artists from Glouster. But this fantasy house takes a step closer to luxury than what could generally be fathomed.
